text: Those of you who are saying that the movie does not follow the book all that much are forgetting that the book had a flawed message.Â  Saying "some people just have bad days" makes less senseÂ when most of the things that happen ARE THE MAIN CHARACTER'S FAULT. Gum in his hair when he woke up? He went to sleep with gum in his mouth. Teacher liked someone else's drawing instead of his?Â  He didn't draw ANYTHING.Â  THIS movie strengthens the message by taking people who never had a bad day and having them learn how to deal with it with someone with experience.Â  I for one, have been interested in this since I sawÂ the press release (which DOES mention the gum scene by the by, so they aren't ignoring the book completely) and this trailer just strengthens that interest.
